Is South Africa losing its battle against COVID-19? To discuss this, eNCA's Faith Mangope speaks to Prof. Koleka Mlisana, co-chairperson of the Ministerial Advisory Committee. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As COVID-19 cases increase at a concerning rate, the head of the Ministerial Advisory Committee says tighter restrictions need to be implemented.
More than 7,000 cases have been recorded nationally in the past 24 hours. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Gauteng may get tougher restrictions Professor Koleka Mlisana is concerned and says it's evident social gatherings are adding to the surge. For the full interview, watch the video above.